<POST>
<POSTER> &quot;eb...@hotmail.com&quot; &lt;eb...@hotmail.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-07-15T22:42:00 </POSTDATE>
I used to frequent alt.movies.silent a few years ago and would also
post on occasion.  At the time, the group was like a breath of fresh
air to me: a vibrant and intelligent community of online silent film
fans.  There were many far-reaching discussions with thought-provoking
and funny posts and it made me feel a little less alone as a young man
with obscure interests.  After I graduated college, worked for a
newspaper, grew more interested in later arthouse and cult films,
travelled in Europe, and then switched to law school, I lost track of
the group and stopped checking in.  But there were definitely times
when I missed it.

Now, I may be off-base here, but it seems as though things have gone
downhill at alt.movies.silent.  A lot of the people I remember from
the past (Federica, Precode, Vitaphone) are absent.  I don't see any
in-depth discussions like there used to be.  I find this very poignant
and I wonder when and why this happened.
</POST>
