&quot;Vitaphone&quot; (Jeff) here, and still a regular reader at that --- but I too
have noticed sweeping changes since first posting here five or so years ago,
and not for the better.   As someone else noted, the group is frequently
plagued by &quot;trolls,&quot; but I was far more disheartened by the public battles,
attempts to defame and maul --- many of which succeeded apparently,  and an
overall bitter tone that still prevails.

I simply can't understand why a group who's members all share the same
interest and all work towards a common goal --- that of keeping these films
&quot;alive&quot; --- can often be so self-destructive
and hurtful.

Vintage film's worst enemy seems to be it's dearest friends. A puzzle, that.

Jeff

