I first found this place around 1999 or 2000, when it was a tight-knit
group of silent movie/early talkie enthusiasts, many of whom knew each
other. A LOT of quality regular posters. I was a particularly annoying
jackass for quite a while, but eventually learned to shut up and not
get in the way of the people who really knew their stuff. Many--most?--
of these people don't visit a.m.s. anymore, driven away by usenet
trolls and spam posts. There's also the weariness factor--how many
times can we argue Chaplin vs. Keaton vs. Lloyd? '42 Gold Rush vs. '25
Gold Rush?

I have to say, though, that battles over the usual crap--BOAN,
Riefenstahl, Harry Langdon--were just as contentious, and occasionally
hurtful, back in the good old days.

