I do remember some condescending and unnecessarily harsh posts, but I
don't think it was ever that bad (circa 2003).  Actually, I look back
on the arguments about BOAN, blackface, Charlie Chan (the aborted Fox
Movie Channel festival), ect. very positively on the basis of the
sheer number of intelligent points that were made.

I also remember some particularly beautiful posts about W.C. Fields,
around the time when TCM ran a festival of all of his films.  And
Wheeler and Woolsey!  Is the author of the book about them still here?
I was probably a little more geered toward 30s comedy (that decade in
general, really) than silents at the time that I used to post.

I really liked the threads with people's memories of AMC at the time
when that channel took a sudden turn from the worst.  If and when this
happens to TCM (God forbid), I would hope to find a similar discussion
here.

But it is nice to see some of the regulars never left.  What happened
to Federica? Harlett O'Dowd?

