Fred got tired of the flaming and is moderator of the yahoo silent
film group.

I think there is mostly a fatigue factor here. And these groups, in
sort of google-like fashion, would extinguish themselves, since FAQ's
tend to be reductive, and by searching the group you could find many
prior answers and opinions to the same questions.  I mean--how many
more times is someone going to ask about the same Nosferatu score?

That always leaves discussions of festivals, new scores...things like
that. But I liken this place to a coffee shop, where people ultimately
come and go...but after about 2000 or so, when groups like this were
discovered by new Internet users, not a lot of new blood since, and a
lot of favorite customers have moved on. In other words, we may have
hit the maximum saturation about that time, for silent film fan
Anglophones.
